text: Sanabares (Greek: ϹΑΝΑΒΑΡΟΥ Sanabarou; 135-160 CE) was an Indo-Parthian king. He was the last Indo-Parthian king to rule in Sakastan and south Arachosia.Indo-Greek and Indo-Scythian Coinage - Michael Mitchiner - 1976, Volumes 7 à 9 - Pages 670, 717 and 770 == References == == Sources == * * Category:Year of death unknown Category:Year of birth unknown Category:135 births Category:Iranian people
